<p>What is the way out?</p>

<p>When incomes fall sharply, private individuals cut back consumption. When private consumption falls sharply, businesses stop investing. Since both of these are voluntary decisions, there is no way to force people to spend more and/or coerce businesses to invest more in the current scenario.</p>

<p>The same logic holds for exports and imports as well.</p>

<p>Under the circumstances, there is only one engine that can boost GDP and that is the government (G). Only when government spend more â€” either by building roads and bridges and paying salaries or by directly handing out money â€” can the economy revive in the short to medium term. If the government does not spend adequately enough then the economy will take a long time to recover.</p>

